<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-08-28T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-08-28T12:00:00-05:00" n="317" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d317">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 103.93/69: Telegram</note>
                    <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                                <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss></hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-08-28T13:00:00-04:00">August 28, 1919—1
                            p.m.</date><lb/>[Received August 29—2:47 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                    <p>2989. For Polk. Your 3604, August 9, 7 p.m. Please notify press associations
                        and newspaper correspondents that transmission of their news matter by
                        wireless from Paris to America will be discontinued, the last filings to be
                        made in Paris on August 30th; the news report and editorial summary
                        heretofore transmitted by the New York office of the mission will be
                        continued by the Department.</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
